doc.after: Finnair Plc (Finnish: Finnair Oyj, Swedish: Finnair Abp)[5] is the flag carrier and largest airline of Finland, with its headquarters in Vantaa and its main hub at Helsinki-Vantaa Airport. Finnair and its subsidiaries dominate both domestic and international air travel in Finland. Its major shareholder is the government of Finland, with 55.8%[6] of the shares.
